        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 2:18PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 218 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Nutt, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nutt, Uvas Valley, and Macho Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
